    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to the pan with<strong> </strong>your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 3-4 min or until the pepper is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1643201870885-x200.jpg",
